fr.csvbang.annotation
Annotation Type CsvField

@Target(value={FIELD,METHOD})
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Inherited
@Documented
public @interface CsvField

Annotation in order to define a CSV field

Version:
0.0.1
Author:
Tony EMMA

Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.String defaultIfNull
          Default value if the value is null.
 boolean deleteIfNull
          Delete field if the value is null.
 java.lang.String name
          Name of field in CSV file.
 int position
           Position of field in file.
 

name

public abstract java.lang.String name
Name of field in CSV file. If no name is defined, the name of member (field or method) is selected. By default no name is defined.

Returns:
name
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
""

position

public abstract int position

Position of field in file. The first position of the first field is 1. It is not required that position numbers follow. The default position is -1.

If no position is required you can set a negative position. If you want to override a CsvField annotation in sub class, you must set a negative value other than -1

Returns:
the position of field
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
-1

defaultIfNull

public abstract java.lang.String defaultIfNull
Default value if the value is null. By default, it's an empty string

Returns:
default value.
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
""

deleteIfNull

public abstract boolean deleteIfNull
Delete field if the value is null. Delete field only for the current record. By default false.

Returns:
True if we must delete field.
Since:
0.0.1
Default:
false
